ange students, including {{ill|Tsuda Umeko|ja|津田梅子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, departed Yokohama for the United States. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1872|ja|1872|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 12|ja|12月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A governmental edict abolished traditional formal attire (such as the kabuto and hakama) in favor of Western dress.
