== Events == * [[Kaika Tennō]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|157 BC|ja|紀元前157|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/157 BC|qq=}} [[:en:December 11|December 11]]) – The 9th Emperor, [[:en:Emperor Kaika|Kaika Tennō]], ascended to the throne.{{Citation needed|date=2021-03|qq=}} * [[Kenkō (era)|Kenkō]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|316|ja|316|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/316|qq=}} [[:en:December 12|December 12]]) – The Western Jin Dynasty collapsed. * [[Genroku]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1688|ja|1688|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1688|qq=}} [[:en:December 4|December 4]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi]] selected his aide, [[:en:Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu|Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu]], as his official (sōi) and advisor. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1871|ja|1871|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1871|qq=}} [[:en:December 23|December 23]]) – Five of Japan’s first female exchange students, including [[:en:Tsuda Umeko|Tsuda Umeko]], departed Yokohama for the United States. * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1872|ja|1872|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1872|qq=}} [[:en:December 12|December 12]]) – A governmental edict abolished traditional formal attire (such as the kabuto and hakama) in favor of Western dress.
== Births == * [[Chishō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1178|ja|1178|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1178|qq=}} [[:en:December 22|December 22]]) – [[:en:Emperor Antoku|Emperor Antoku]], the 81st Emperor of Japan (died {{ill|1185|ja|1185|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1185|qq=}}).<ref>{{Kotobank|安徳天皇|qq=}}</ref>
== Deaths == * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1864|ja|1864|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1864|qq=}} [[:en:December 10|December 10]]) – [[:en:Kunishi Shinano|Kunishi Chisanao]], a senior retainer (家老) of the Chōshū Domain (born {{ill|1842|ja|1842|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1842|qq=}}). * In the same Genji 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] 1864, December 10) – {{ill|Fukuhara Motomi|ja|福原元僴|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuhara Motomi|qq=}}, another senior retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born {{ill|1815|ja|1815|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1815|qq=}}).
