'''November 12''' is the 12th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|1=Butsumetsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10886789}}.

== Events ==
* [[:en:Kaika Tennō|Kaika Tennō]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|157 BC|ja|紀元前157|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/157 BC|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} {{ill|December 11|en|December 11|WD=Q2363|lt=December 11|1=December 11}}) – The 9th Emperor, {{ill|Emperor Kaika|en|Emperor Kaika|WD=Q333548|lt=Kaika Tennō|1=Emperor Kaika}}, ascended to the throne.{{Citation needed|date=2021-03|qq=}}
* [[Kenkō (era)|Kenkō]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|316|en|316|WD=Q31894|lt=316|1=316}} {{ill|December 12|en|December 12|WD=Q2369|lt=December 12|1=December 12}}) – The Western Jin Dynasty collapsed.
* {{ill|Genroku|en|Genroku|WD=Q1325001|lt=Genroku|1=Genroku}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1688|en|1688|WD=Q7671|lt=1688|1=1688}} {{ill|December 4|en|December 4|WD=Q2310|lt=December 4|1=December 4}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|en|Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|WD=Q313745|lt=Tokugawa Tsunayoshi|1=Tokugawa Tsunayoshi}} selected his aide, {{ill|Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu|en|Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu|WD=Q846911|lt=Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu|1=Yanagisawa Yoshiyasu}}, as his official (sōi) and advisor.
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1871|en|1871|WD=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}} {{ill|December 23|en|December 23|WD=Q2676|lt=December 23|1=December 23}}) – Five of Japan’s first female exchange students, including {{ill|Tsuda Umeko|en|Tsuda Umeko|WD=Q514524|lt=Tsuda Umeko|1=Tsuda Umeko}}, departed Yokohama for the United States.
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1872|en|1872|WD=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} {{ill|December 12|en|December 12|WD=Q2369|lt=December 12|1=December 12}}) – A governmental edict abolished traditional formal attire (such as the kabuto and hakama) in favor of Western dress.

== Births ==
* [[Chishō]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1178|en|1178|WD=Q19696|lt=1178|1=1178}} {{ill|December 22|en|December 22|WD=Q2636|lt=December 22|1=December 22}}) – {{ill|Emperor Antoku|en|Emperor Antoku|WD=Q316651|lt=Emperor Antoku|1=Emperor Antoku}}, the 81st Emperor of Japan (died {{ill|1185|en|1185|WD=Q19729|lt=1185|1=1185}}).<ref>{{Kotobank|安徳天皇|qq=}}</ref>

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Genji era|en|Genji era|WD=Q1325419|lt=Genji|1=Genji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1864|en|1864|WD=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}} {{ill|December 10|en|December 10|WD=Q2302|lt=December 10|1=December 10}}) – {{ill|Kunishi Shinano|en|Kunishi Shinano|WD=Q6444766|lt=Kunishi Chisanao|1=Kunishi Shinano}}, a senior retainer (家老) of the Chōshū Domain (born {{ill|1842|en|1842|WD=Q7625|lt=1842|1=1842}}).
* In the same Genji 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} 1864, December 10) – {{ill|Fukuhara Motomi|ja|福原元僴|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukuhara Motomi|1=Echigo Fukuhara|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11591845}}, another senior retainer of the Chōshū Domain (born {{ill|1815|en|1815|WD=Q6948|lt=1815|1=1815}}).

